## Overview

This document outlines the best practices, conventions, and standards for managing the **{{PROJECT_NAME}}** infrastructure using Infrastructure as Code (IaC). All infrastructure must be version-controlled, peer-reviewed, and deployed through automated pipelines. Manual changes to any environment are strictly prohibited.

## Technology Stack

- **IaC Tool**: {{IAC_TOOL}} (e.g., Terraform, AWS CDK, Pulumi)
- **Cloud Provider**: {{CLOUD_PROVIDER}} (e.g., AWS, GCP, Azure)
- **State Backend**: {{IAC_STATE_BACKEND}} (e.g., S3 + DynamoDB, Terraform Cloud, GCS)
- **Secret Management**: {{SECRETS_MANAGER}} (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault)
- **CI/CD Platform**: {{CICD_PLATFORM}} (e.g., GitHub Actions, GitLab CI)
- **Container Registry**: {{CONTAINER_REGISTRY}} (optional, e.g., ECR, GCR, ACR)

