## Folder Structure

All infrastructure code lives under the `infrastructure/` directory at the repository root.

```
infrastructure/
├── modules/                    # Reusable, self-contained infrastructure modules
│   ├── networking/             # VPC, subnets, route tables, peering
│   ├── compute/                # EC2, ECS, Lambda, GKE, etc.
│   ├── database/               # RDS, DynamoDB, Cloud SQL, etc.
│   ├── storage/                # S3, GCS, Azure Blob, etc.
│   ├── security/               # IAM roles, policies, KMS keys, WAF
│   ├── observability/          # CloudWatch, Datadog, logging, alerting
│   └── dns/                    # Route53, Cloud DNS, domain management
├── environments/               # Per-environment root configurations
│   ├── dev/
│   │   ├── main.tf             # (or main.ts / __main__.py)
│   │   ├── variables.tf
│   │   ├── outputs.tf
│   │   └── terraform.tfvars    # Non-secret variable values only
│   ├── staging/
│   │   └── ...
│   └── prod/
│       └── ...
├── global/                     # Resources shared across all environments
│   ├── iam/                    # Cross-account roles, OIDC providers
│   ├── dns/                    # Apex domain, delegated zones
│   └── state/                  # Remote state backend bootstrap
├── scripts/                    # Helper shell/Python scripts for infra tasks
├── docs/                       # Architecture diagrams, runbooks, ADRs
├── tests/                      # Infrastructure unit and integration tests
│   ├── unit/
│   └── integration/
└── .tool-versions              # Pin tool versions (tfenv, cdktf, etc.)
```

**Rules:**
- Every environment directory is a fully independent root — no symlinks between environment configs.
- Modules are versioned and sourced by environments; environments never copy-paste module code.
- The `global/` directory is for truly cross-environment resources only; keep it minimal.
- Never commit `.terraform/`, `node_modules/`, `cdk.out/`, or `.pulumi/` directories.

