## Tagging Strategy

Every resource that supports tags **must** have the following mandatory tags:

| Tag Key | Value | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `Project` | `{{PROJECT_NAME}}` | Project identifier |
| `Environment` | `dev` / `staging` / `prod` | Deployment environment |
| `Component` | e.g., `api`, `database`, `networking` | Functional component |
| `ManagedBy` | `terraform` / `cdk` / `pulumi` | IaC tool managing the resource |
| `Owner` | Team or squad name | Ownership for cost allocation |
| `CostCenter` | Cost center code | FinOps / billing allocation |

Optional but recommended tags:

| Tag Key | Value |
|---|---|
| `Repository` | GitHub/GitLab repo URL |
| `CreatedAt` | ISO 8601 date |
| `DataClassification` | `public`, `internal`, `confidential`, `restricted` |

**Rules:**
- Define a `locals` block (or equivalent) with all mandatory tags and merge it into every resource.
- Tag enforcement must be implemented via cloud policy (AWS SCP, GCP Organization Policy, Azure Policy).
- Untagged resources in production trigger an automated alert.

