## Environment Management

Three standard environments exist. Each environment is isolated — no shared resources, no shared networking, no shared IAM across environments.

| Environment | Purpose | Auto-Deploy | Approval Required |
|---|---|---|---|
| `dev` | Feature development and integration | Yes (on merge to `main`) | No |
| `staging` | Pre-production validation, load testing | Yes (on merge to `main`) | No |
| `prod` | Production traffic | No | Yes (manual gate) |

**Rules:**
- Production environments must be deployed from tagged releases only, never from branch commits.
- `dev` and `staging` can be destroyed and recreated on demand.
- Cross-environment access (e.g., `dev` reading `prod` data) is prohibited at the IAM level.
- Each environment must have its own separate cloud account (or project/subscription) to enforce blast-radius isolation.

